  "text": "We screened for saRNAs targeting OCT4, SOX2, and NANOG genes by regular RT-PCR and confirmed the results by Western blotting and RT-qPCR in human fibroblasts transfected with saRNA for 96 h. The preliminary screening results showed that the mRNA and protein levels of OCT4 and SOX2 were altered by several saRNAs: S278 activated SOX2, while O134 and O38 activated OCT4 (Fig.  1) . This is the first report of saRNAs for OCT4 and SOX2. Although the saRNA dsNanog752 has been reported to activate NANOG, [CITATION_1] we also found that our designed dsRNA N185 activated NANOG, although this response was minor. All positive results were confirmed by gel extraction and sequencing (Additional file 3, Suppl. Figs. S1-S3). Other dsRNAs tested, such as O302, O619, S134, S227, N35, and N116, showed no effect and were not studied further.",
